Comment_glosser: Turkic Ainu is a secret language with largely Persian vocabulary. The numerals seem to be Persian as well apart from some unclear cases and some vowel contractions (e.g. in 4).
The forms of 40-90 are rather ‘the fourth’, ‘the fifth’ etc. in Persian. This is either a mistake in the dataset or a deviation from the Persian numeral system in this language.
